# LazyNevis

Read `AGENTS.md` and `RTK.md` before non-trivial edits, plus relevant `openspec/specs/*/spec.md`. Use `openspec/README.md` for behavior/schema/security/cross-module changes, `DESIGN.md` for visual work, and `docs/architecture/release.md` for release work.

## Stack
- Tauri v2 desktop app.
- Rust backend in `src-tauri/src/`.
- React 19 + TypeScript frontend in `src/`.
- Vite 8 + Tailwind v4 + Zustand + i18next.
- Bun package manager; use `/Users/lucas/.bun/bin/bun` if PATH lacks `bun`.

## Required Patterns
- No TypeScript `any`.
- No new hardcoded user-visible strings; add locale keys to both `en-US.json` and `pt-BR.json`.
- `useFocusSession()` is only called in `AppShell`.
- Add Tauri wrappers in `src/services/tauri.ts`.
- Mirror Rust payloads/models in `src/types/index.ts`.
- Register new Rust commands in `src-tauri/src/lib.rs`.
- New SQL belongs in `src-tauri/src/db/queries.rs`.
- Keep alert checks in the 1-second ticker in `src-tauri/src/monitor.rs`.
- Keep `rodio::OutputStream` inside the audio background thread.
- Keep LazyNevis in `ALWAYS_IGNORED`.
- Update specs and tests for behavior changes. Keep all adapters named in `AGENTS.md` aligned.

## Validate
```bash
bun run test
bun run build
cargo test --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml
bun run quality
```

Report task IDs, files owned, validation, unresolved risks, and manual actions.

## Known Debt
- Some production Rust panics and inline SQL remain; avoid adding more.
- Some existing hardcoded UI strings remain; avoid adding more.
